	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Cape Town - Four armed men escaped with guns and money
when they hit a cash-in-transit vehicle at Pick n Pay in Parow on Saturday
morning, Western Cape police have reported. Police spokesperson Lieutenant Colonel Andre Traut said
the gang struck at 08:50. “During the collection of cash boxes at a grocery store
in Parow, four armed suspects robbed security personnel transporting cash of
their firearms and an undisclosed amount of cash,” he said. “No shots were fire and no injuries were sustained.” No arrests have yet been made and the incident is under
investigation, Traut confirmed.   24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.